  "title": "Weighted Job Scheduling",
  "difficulty": "HARD",
  "statement": "You are given `n` jobs, each with a start time, end time, and value. You can only work on one job at a time. Jobs that share even one time unit **conflict**. Select a non-conflicting subset to **maximize total value**.\n\n**Input:** First line: n. Next n lines: start end value.\n**Output:** Maximum total value.",
  "constraints": "- 1 \u2264 n \u2264 10\u2075\n- 1 \u2264 start < end \u2264 10\u2079\n- 1 \u2264 value \u2264 10\u2076",
