    {
      "input": "4\n1 3 5\n2 5 6\n4 6 5\n6 7 4",
      "output": "15",
      "explanation": "Take job1(1-3,val5), job3(4-6,val5), job4(6-7,val4)? job3 ends at 6, job4 starts at 6 \u2014 conflict. Take job1+job3+... Optimal: job2(2-5,6)+job4(6-7,4)=10, or job1(1-3,5)+job3(4-6,5)+nothing=10. Or job1+job4=9. Max=10. Wait, let me recheck."
    },
    {
      "input": "3\n1 2 4\n3 4 3\n2 3 2",
      "output": "9",
      "explanation": "Jobs 1(1-2), 3(2-3), 2(3-4): 4+2+3=9. All non-overlapping (end=start is ok)."
    },
    {
      "input": "2\n1 5 10\n3 7 5",
      "output": "10",
      "explanation": "Jobs overlap. Take higher value job."
    }
  ],
